      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "MarkdownNote"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "## SeedVR2 image refine\n\nNo prompt needed — load an image and run. SeedVR2 *re-synthesizes* detail\n(pores, fabric, hair), unlike ESRGAN which only sharpens existing edges.\n`LoadImage -> SeedVR2VideoUpscaler -> SaveImage`.\n\n---\n### Turn on the speed-up (RunPod / Linux)\nAfter `python3 script/install_custom_nodes.py` finishes on the VM, **SageAttention 2\nis already installed** (auto, Linux only). In the **SeedVR2LoadDiTModel** node change\n**`attention_mode`: `sdpa` -> `sageattn_2`**. That's the whole speed-up.\n\n### Pick attention_mode by GPU\n| GPU you rent | Best attention_mode | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| A100 / A40 / A6000 / L40 / 4090 (Ampere/Ada) | `sageattn_2` | auto-installed; the real win over sdpa |\n| H100 / H200 (Hopper) | `sageattn_2` (or flash_attn_3) | sageattn_2 is faster |\n| B200 / RTX 50xx (Blackwell) | `sageattn_3` | needs a separate SageAttention 3 source build |\n| anything, no extras | `sdpa` | already uses built-in FlashAttention-2 |\n\nSkip `flash_attn_2` — barely faster than `sdpa` (sdpa already runs FA2 internally),\nnot worth the build.\n\n### One more free speed lever\nOn a big GPU (48 GB+) set **`blocks_to_swap`: `36 -> 0`** in the DiT loader. 36 is a\nsafe won't-OOM default; 0 disables CPU offload and avoids GPU<->CPU transfer overhead.\n\n---\n### Other knobs (SeedVR2VideoUpscaler)\n- **resolution** = target SHORT edge: `1440` ~ 2K, `2160` ~ near-4K, `4096` = 4K.\n- **color_correction** = `lab` keeps colors faithful.\n- VAE tiling (tile 1024 / overlap 128) is the memory bottleneck — shrink tiles if you OOM.\n- ~14 GB DiT + VAE auto-download to `models/SEEDVR2` on first run.\n\n**Mac:** this node is CUDA-only and the installer skips it on macOS — nothing to run here.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
